  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A change on the day he went to teach the MPs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is hereby informed that the talk on \"Current Economic Status and Prospects of Sri Lanka\" which was scheduled to be held on Tuesday 30th August 2022 from 2.00pm to 4.00pm at the Parliament Complex, will not be held on that day due to unavoidable reasons and the program will be held on Wednesday 31st August 2022 at 4.00pm. From 2:30 p.m. The Deputy Speaker Hon. Ajith Rajapaksa announced to the Parliament today (29) that arrangements have been made to hold the committee meeting at Room No. 01 of the Parliament Complex until 4.30.",
        "In parliamentary debates, this program is to be conducted by the Governor of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka, Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe, to confirm the active participation of the members of parliament in relation to financial matters and to create an effective discourse on the current economic situation of the country and the future economic path."
      ],
